item.title: Vodafone VIP: Fashion Photography With F1's Lewis Hamilton & Jenson Button
item.description:
Vodafone VIP: Fashion Photography With F1's Lewis Hamilton & Jenson Button
http://tiny.ly/6Weg Another Vodafone VIP classic as Vodafone McLaren Mercedes F1's Lewis Hamilton and Jenson Button are invited to a photo shoot with a difference. Rather than being the focus of the shoot, this time the famous Formula 1 duo are let loose as photographers directing an 'eccentric British summer' fashion shoot. This is a photo shoot with a twist as Hamilton and Button discover their wacky, creative flair and are tasked with everything from choosing the wardrobe, to selecting props and taking the final shots. With Lewis behind the camera and Jenson (as his assistant!) directing the models this is a great bit of cheeky fun and an amusing distraction for Jenson and Lewis before they get behind the wheel at the next Formula 1 2011 Grand Prix. What is Vodafone VIP? Find out more here http://tiny.ly/6Weg

item.title: Favorite Products of June
item.description:
Favorite Products of June
You can check out BeingGirl at: http://www.youtube.com/BeingGirl  I just wanna say, BeingGirl actually visited my High School when I was a teen girl and they actually taught me everything about growing up. Since I have a large following of young girls, they asked me to share the joy with their helpful channel. I am sharing their channel because I feel 'Puberty' is a touchy subject even within such a girly community. My parents never actually gave me 'the talk' (lol typical asian parents) so I really hope you girlies will find 'BeingGirl' helpful. I know I did and I hope you guys will. Here are my Favourite products of the month of June. There's a mixture of drugstore and high end but I have really been enjoying this month's favourites. Products mentioned: Revlon Colorstay soft & smooth lipstick in Creamy coral (Can be found in your local drugstore) Physiogel A.I lotion (I bought mine in my local pharmacy) Dior AirFlash Spray foundation (Found in your nearest Dior counter although I had to get my friend to buy it for me from UK because Hong Kong doesn't carry it) St Ives (Can be found in your local drugstore. AprilAthena7 popped this as a gift for me ^_^). Lioele Blooming Gloss no2 (The company sent me this but in HK, I buy Lioele from ColorMix) You can read a detailed review of the Physiogel A.I lotion by visiting my website http://www.bubzbeauty.com Check out my girlies on Youtube. They are beautiful, smart and they know their stuff. Since I mentioned them in this video, I figured I'll list their channels and hopefully you'll adore them as much as I do. youtube.com/RAEview youtube.com/Aprilathena7 youtube.com/Hollyannaeree Music: K will "My heart is beating' instrumental.
